246__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_cow(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
247{
248 if (!aff)
249 return NULL((void*)0);
250
251 if (aff->ref == 1)
252 return aff;
253 aff->ref--;
254 return isl_aff_dup(aff);
255}

257__isl_null isl_aff *isl_aff_free(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
258{
259 if (!aff)
260 return NULL((void*)0);
261
262 if (--aff->ref > 0)
263 return NULL((void*)0);
264
265 isl_local_space_free(aff->ls);
266 isl_vec_free(aff->v);
267
268 free(aff);
269
270 return NULL((void*)0);
271}

280uint32_t isl_aff_get_hash(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff)

0xFF; } while(0); do { hash *= 16777619; hash ^= ((ls_hash) >>
16) & 0xFF; } while(0); do { hash *= 16777619; hash ^= (
(ls_hash) >> 24) & 0xFF; } while(0); } while(0);

296/* Externally, an isl_aff has a map space, but internally, the
297 * ls field corresponds to the domain of that space.
298 */
299int isl_aff_dim(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff, enum isl_dim_type type)
300{
301 if (!aff)
302 return 0;
303 if (type == isl_dim_out)
304 return 1;
305 if (type == isl_dim_in)
306 type = isl_dim_set;
307 return isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, type);
308}

311 * in "aff".
312 * Return -1 if no such dimension can be found.
313 */
314int isl_aff_find_dim_by_name(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff, enum isl_dim_type type,
315 const char *name)

317 if (!aff)

320 return -1;

322 type = isl_dim_set;
323 return isl_local_space_find_dim_by_name(aff->ls, type, name);
324}

374__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_reset_domain_space(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
375 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *dim)
376{

386error:

403/* Reorder the coefficients of the affine expression based
404 * on the given reodering.
405 * The reordering r is assumed to have been extended with the local
406 * variables.
407 */
408static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_vec *vec_reorder(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_vec *vec,
409 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_reordering *r, int n_div)
410{
411 isl_vec *res;
412 int i;
413
414 if (!vec || !r)
415 goto error;
416
417 res = isl_vec_alloc(vec->ctx,
418 2 + isl_space_dim(r->dim, isl_dim_all) + n_div);
419 isl_seq_cpy(res->el, vec->el, 2);
420 isl_seq_clr(res->el + 2, res->size - 2);
421 for (i = 0; i < r->len; ++i)
422 isl_int_set(res->el[2 + r->pos[i]], vec->el[2 + i])isl_sioimath_set((res->el[2 + r->pos[i]]), *(vec->el
[2 + i]));
423
424 isl_reordering_free(r);
425 isl_vec_free(vec);
426 return res;
427error:
428 isl_vec_free(vec);
429 isl_reordering_free(r);
430 return NULL((void*)0);
431}

433/* Reorder the dimensions of the domain of "aff" according
434 * to the given reordering.
435 */
436__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_realign_domain(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
437 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_reordering *r)
438{
439 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
440 if (!aff)
441 goto error;
442
443 r = isl_reordering_extend(r, aff->ls->div->n_row);
444 aff->v = vec_reorder(aff->v, isl_reordering_copy(r),
445 aff->ls->div->n_row);
446 aff->ls = isl_local_space_realign(aff->ls, r);
447
448 if (!aff->v || !aff->ls)
449 return isl_aff_free(aff);
450
451 return aff;
452error:
453 isl_aff_free(aff);
454 isl_reordering_free(r);
455 return NULL((void*)0);
456}

458__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_align_params(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
459 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *model)
460{
461 if (!aff || !model)
462 goto error;
463
464 if (!isl_space_match(aff->ls->dim, isl_dim_param,
465 model, isl_dim_param)) {
466 isl_reordering *exp;
467
468 model = isl_space_drop_dims(model, isl_dim_in,
469 0, isl_space_dim(model, isl_dim_in));
470 model = isl_space_drop_dims(model, isl_dim_out,
471 0, isl_space_dim(model, isl_dim_out));
472 exp = isl_parameter_alignment_reordering(aff->ls->dim, model);
473 exp = isl_reordering_extend_space(exp,
474 isl_aff_get_domain_space(aff));
475 aff = isl_aff_realign_domain(aff, exp);
476 }
477
478 isl_space_free(model);
479 return aff;
480error:
481 isl_space_free(model);
482 isl_aff_free(aff);
483 return NULL((void*)0);
484}

486/* Is "aff" obviously equal to zero?
487 *
488 * If the denominator is zero, then "aff" is not equal to zero.
489 */
490isl_bool isl_aff_plain_is_zero(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff)
491{
492 if (!aff)
493 return isl_bool_error;
494
495 if (isl_int_is_zero(aff->v->el[0])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(aff->v->el[0])) == 0))
496 return isl_bool_false;
497 return isl_seq_first_non_zero(aff->v->el + 1, aff->v->size - 1) < 0;
498}
499
500/* Does "aff" represent NaN?
501 */
502isl_bool isl_aff_is_nan(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff)
503{
504 if (!aff)
505 return isl_bool_error;
506
507 return isl_seq_first_non_zero(aff->v->el, 2) < 0;
508}
509
510/* Does "pa" involve any NaNs?
511 */
512isl_bool isl_pw_aff_involves_nan(__isl_keep isl_pw_aff *pa)
513{
514 int i;
515
516 if (!pa)
517 return isl_bool_error;
518 if (pa->n == 0)
519 return isl_bool_false;
520
521 for (i = 0; i < pa->n; ++i) {
522 isl_bool is_nan = isl_aff_is_nan(pa->p[i].aff);
523 if (is_nan < 0 || is_nan)
524 return is_nan;
525 }
526
527 return isl_bool_false;
528}
529
530/* Are "aff1" and "aff2" obviously equal?
531 *
532 * NaN is not equal to anything, not even to another NaN.
533 */
534isl_bool isl_aff_plain_is_equal(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff1,
535 __isl_keep isl_aff *aff2)
536{
537 isl_bool equal;
538
539 if (!aff1 || !aff2)
540 return isl_bool_error;
541
542 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff1) || isl_aff_is_nan(aff2))
543 return isl_bool_false;
544
545 equal = isl_local_space_is_equal(aff1->ls, aff2->ls);
546 if (equal < 0 || !equal)
547 return equal;
548
549 return isl_vec_is_equal(aff1->v, aff2->v);
550}
551
552/* Return the common denominator of "aff" in "v".
553 *
554 * We cannot return anything meaningful in case of a NaN.
555 */
556int isl_aff_get_denominator(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff, isl_int *v)
557{
558 if (!aff)
559 return -1;
560 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff))

749/* Replace the constant term of "aff" by "v".
750 *
751 * A NaN is unaffected by this operation.
752 */
753__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_set_constant_val(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
754 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_val *v)
755{
756 if (!aff || !v)
757 goto error;
758
759 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff)) {
760 isl_val_free(v);
761 return aff;
762 }
763
764 if (!isl_val_is_rat(v))
765 isl_die(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "expecting rational value", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 766); goto error; } while (0)
766 "expecting rational value", goto error)do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "expecting rational value", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 766); goto error; } while (0);
767
768 if (isl_int_eq(aff->v->el[1], v->n)(isl_sioimath_cmp(*(aff->v->el[1]), *(v->n)) == 0) &&
769 isl_int_eq(aff->v->el[0], v->d)(isl_sioimath_cmp(*(aff->v->el[0]), *(v->d)) == 0)) {
770 isl_val_free(v);
771 return aff;
772 }
773
774 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
775 if (!aff)
776 goto error;
777 aff->v = isl_vec_cow(aff->v);
778 if (!aff->v)
779 goto error;
780
781 if (isl_int_eq(aff->v->el[0], v->d)(isl_sioimath_cmp(*(aff->v->el[0]), *(v->d)) == 0)) {
782 isl_int_set(aff->v->el[1], v->n)isl_sioimath_set((aff->v->el[1]), *(v->n));
783 } else if (isl_int_is_one(v->d)(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(v->d), 1) == 0)) {
784 isl_int_mul(aff->v->el[1], aff->v->el[0], v->n)isl_sioimath_mul((aff->v->el[1]), *(aff->v->el[0]
), *(v->n));
785 } else {
786 isl_seq_scale(aff->v->el + 1,
787 aff->v->el + 1, v->d, aff->v->size - 1);
788 isl_int_mul(aff->v->el[1], aff->v->el[0], v->n)isl_sioimath_mul((aff->v->el[1]), *(aff->v->el[0]
), *(v->n));
789 isl_int_mul(aff->v->el[0], aff->v->el[0], v->d)isl_sioimath_mul((aff->v->el[0]), *(aff->v->el[0]
), *(v->d));
790 aff->v = isl_vec_normalize(aff->v);
791 if (!aff->v)
792 goto error;
793 }
794
795 isl_val_free(v);
796 return aff;
797error:
798 isl_aff_free(aff);
799 isl_val_free(v);
800 return NULL((void*)0);
801}

822 return isl_aff_free(aff);

[0]), *(v));

1213__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_add_coefficient_si(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,

1234/* Return the negation of "aff".
1235 *
1236 * As a special case, -NaN = NaN.
1237 */
1238__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_neg(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
1239{
1240 if (!aff)
1241 return NULL((void*)0);
1242 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff))
1243 return aff;
1244 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
1245 if (!aff)
1246 return NULL((void*)0);
1247 aff->v = isl_vec_cow(aff->v);
1248 if (!aff->v)
1249 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1250
1251 isl_seq_neg(aff->v->el + 1, aff->v->el + 1, aff->v->size - 1);
1252
1253 return aff;
1254}

1256/* Remove divs from the local space that do not appear in the affine
1257 * expression.
1258 * We currently only remove divs at the end.
1259 * Some intermediate divs may also not appear directly in the affine
1260 * expression, but we would also need to check that no other divs are
1261 * defined in terms of them.
1262 */
1263__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_remove_unused_divs(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
1264{
1265 int pos;
1266 int off;
1267 int n;
1268
1269 if (!aff)
1270 return NULL((void*)0);
1271
1272 n = isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1273 off = isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1274
1275 pos = isl_seq_last_non_zero(aff->v->el + 1 + off, n) + 1;
1276 if (pos == n)
1277 return aff;
1278
1279 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
1280 if (!aff)
1281 return NULL((void*)0);
1282
1283 aff->ls = isl_local_space_drop_dims(aff->ls, isl_dim_div, pos, n - pos);
1284 aff->v = isl_vec_drop_els(aff->v, 1 + off + pos, n - pos);
1285 if (!aff->ls || !aff->v)
1286 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1287
1288 return aff;
1289}
1290
1291/* Given two affine expressions "p" of length p_len (including the
1292 * denominator and the constant term) and "subs" of length subs_len,
1293 * plug in "subs" for the variable at position "pos".
1294 * The variables of "subs" and "p" are assumed to match up to subs_len,
1295 * but "p" may have additional variables.
1296 * "v" is an initialized isl_int that can be used internally.
1297 *
1298 * In particular, if "p" represents the expression
1299 *
1300 * (a i + g)/m
1301 *
1302 * with i the variable at position "pos" and "subs" represents the expression
1303 *
1304 * f/d
1305 *
1306 * then the result represents the expression
1307 *
1308 * (a f + d g)/(m d)
1309 *
1310 */
1311void isl_seq_substitute(isl_int *p, int pos, isl_int *subs,
1312 int p_len, int subs_len, isl_int v)
1313{
1314 isl_int_set(v, p[1 + pos])isl_sioimath_set((v), *(p[1 + pos]));
1315 isl_int_set_si(p[1 + pos], 0)isl_sioimath_set_si((p[1 + pos]), 0);
1316 isl_seq_combine(p + 1, subs[0], p + 1, v, subs + 1, subs_len - 1);
1317 isl_seq_scale(p + subs_len, p + subs_len, subs[0], p_len - subs_len);
1318 isl_int_mul(p[0], p[0], subs[0])isl_sioimath_mul((p[0]), *(p[0]), *(subs[0]));
1319}
1320
1321/* Look for any divs in the aff->ls with a denominator equal to one
1322 * and plug them into the affine expression and any subsequent divs
1323 * that may reference the div.
1324 */
1325static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *plug_in_integral_divs(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
1326{
1327 int i, n;
1328 int len;
1329 isl_int v;
1330 isl_vec *vec;
1331 isl_local_space *ls;
1332 unsigned pos;
1333
1334 if (!aff)
1335 return NULL((void*)0);
1336
1337 n = isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1338 len = aff->v->size;
1339 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
1340 if (!isl_int_is_one(aff->ls->div->row[i][0])(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(aff->ls->div->row[i][0]), 1) ==
0))
1341 continue;
1342 ls = isl_local_space_copy(aff->ls);
1343 ls = isl_local_space_substitute_seq(ls, isl_dim_div, i,
1344 aff->ls->div->row[i], len, i + 1, n - (i + 1));
1345 vec = isl_vec_copy(aff->v);
1346 vec = isl_vec_cow(vec);
1347 if (!ls || !vec)
1348 goto error;
1349
1350 isl_int_init(v)isl_sioimath_init((v));
1351
1352 pos = isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, isl_dim_div) + i;
1353 isl_seq_substitute(vec->el, pos, aff->ls->div->row[i],
1354 len, len, v);
1355
1356 isl_int_clear(v)isl_sioimath_clear((v));
1357
1358 isl_vec_free(aff->v);
1359 aff->v = vec;
1360 isl_local_space_free(aff->ls);
1361 aff->ls = ls;
1362 }
1363
1364 return aff;
1365error:
1366 isl_vec_free(vec);
1367 isl_local_space_free(ls);
1368 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1369}
1370
1371/* Look for any divs j that appear with a unit coefficient inside
1372 * the definitions of other divs i and plug them into the definitions
1373 * of the divs i.
1374 *
1375 * In particular, an expression of the form
1376 *
1377 * floor((f(..) + floor(g(..)/n))/m)
1378 *
1379 * is simplified to
1380 *
1381 * floor((n * f(..) + g(..))/(n * m))
1382 *
1383 * This simplification is correct because we can move the expression
1384 * f(..) into the inner floor in the original expression to obtain
1385 *
1386 * floor(floor((n * f(..) + g(..))/n)/m)
1387 *
1388 * from which we can derive the simplified expression.
1389 */
1390static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *plug_in_unit_divs(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
1391{
1392 int i, j, n;
1393 int off;
1394
1395 if (!aff)
1396 return NULL((void*)0);
1397
1398 n = isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1399 off = isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1400 for (i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
1401 for (j = 0; j < i; ++j) {
1402 if (!isl_int_is_one(aff->ls->div->row[i][1 + off + j])(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(aff->ls->div->row[i][1 + off +
j]), 1) == 0))
1403 continue;
1404 aff->ls = isl_local_space_substitute_seq(aff->ls,
1405 isl_dim_div, j, aff->ls->div->row[j],
1406 aff->v->size, i, 1);
1407 if (!aff->ls)
1408 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1409 }
1410 }
1411
1412 return aff;
1413}
1414
1415/* Swap divs "a" and "b" in "aff", which is assumed to be non-NULL.
1416 *
1417 * Even though this function is only called on isl_affs with a single
1418 * reference, we are careful to only change aff->v and aff->ls together.
1419 */
1420static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *swap_div(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff, int a, int b)
1421{
1422 unsigned off = isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1423 isl_local_space *ls;
1424 isl_vec *v;
1425
1426 ls = isl_local_space_copy(aff->ls);
1427 ls = isl_local_space_swap_div(ls, a, b);
1428 v = isl_vec_copy(aff->v);
1429 v = isl_vec_cow(v);
1430 if (!ls || !v)
1431 goto error;
1432
1433 isl_int_swap(v->el[1 + off + a], v->el[1 + off + b])isl_sioimath_swap((v->el[1 + off + a]), (v->el[1 + off +
b]));
1434 isl_vec_free(aff->v);
1435 aff->v = v;
1436 isl_local_space_free(aff->ls);
1437 aff->ls = ls;
1438
1439 return aff;
1440error:
1441 isl_vec_free(v);
1442 isl_local_space_free(ls);
1443 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1444}
1445
1446/* Merge divs "a" and "b" in "aff", which is assumed to be non-NULL.
1447 *
1448 * We currently do not actually remove div "b", but simply add its
1449 * coefficient to that of "a" and then zero it out.
1450 */
1451static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *merge_divs(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff, int a, int b)
1452{
1453 unsigned off = isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1454
1455 if (isl_int_is_zero(aff->v->el[1 + off + b])(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(aff->v->el[1 + off + b])) == 0))
1456 return aff;
1457
1458 aff->v = isl_vec_cow(aff->v);
1459 if (!aff->v)
1460 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1461
1462 isl_int_add(aff->v->el[1 + off + a],isl_sioimath_add((aff->v->el[1 + off + a]), *(aff->v
->el[1 + off + a]), *(aff->v->el[1 + off + b]))
1463 aff->v->el[1 + off + a], aff->v->el[1 + off + b])isl_sioimath_add((aff->v->el[1 + off + a]), *(aff->v
->el[1 + off + a]), *(aff->v->el[1 + off + b]));
1464 isl_int_set_si(aff->v->el[1 + off + b], 0)isl_sioimath_set_si((aff->v->el[1 + off + b]), 0);
1465
1466 return aff;
1467}
1468
1469/* Sort the divs in the local space of "aff" according to
1470 * the comparison function "cmp_row" in isl_local_space.c,
1471 * combining the coefficients of identical divs.
1472 *
1473 * Reordering divs does not change the semantics of "aff",
1474 * so there is no need to call isl_aff_cow.
1475 * Moreover, this function is currently only called on isl_affs
1476 * with a single reference.
1477 */
1478static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *sort_divs(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
1479{
1480 int i, j, n;
1481
1482 if (!aff)
1483 return NULL((void*)0);
1484
1485 n = isl_aff_dim(aff, isl_dim_div);
1486 for (i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
1487 for (j = i - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
1488 int cmp = isl_mat_cmp_div(aff->ls->div, j, j + 1);
1489 if (cmp < 0)
1490 break;
1491 if (cmp == 0)
1492 aff = merge_divs(aff, j, j + 1);
1493 else
1494 aff = swap_div(aff, j, j + 1);
1495 if (!aff)
1496 return NULL((void*)0);
1497 }
1498 }
1499
1500 return aff;
1501}
1502
1503/* Normalize the representation of "aff".
1504 *
1505 * This function should only be called of "new" isl_affs, i.e.,
1506 * with only a single reference. We therefore do not need to
1507 * worry about affecting other instances.
1508 */
1509__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_normalize(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
1510{
1511 if (!aff)
1512 return NULL((void*)0);
1513 aff->v = isl_vec_normalize(aff->v);
1514 if (!aff->v)
1515 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1516 aff = plug_in_integral_divs(aff);
1517 aff = plug_in_unit_divs(aff);
1518 aff = sort_divs(aff);
1519 aff = isl_aff_remove_unused_divs(aff);
1520 return aff;
1521}

1523/* Given f, return floor(f).
1524 * If f is an integer expression, then just return f.
1525 * If f is a constant, then return the constant floor(f).
1526 * Otherwise, if f = g/m, write g = q m + r,
1527 * create a new div d = [r/m] and return the expression q + d.
1528 * The coefficients in r are taken to lie between -m/2 and m/2.
1529 *
1530 * As a special case, floor(NaN) = NaN.
1531 */
1532__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_floor(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
1533{
1534 int i;
1535 int size;
1536 isl_ctx *ctx;
1537 isl_vec *div;
1538
1539 if (!aff)
1540 return NULL((void*)0);
1541
1542 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff))
1543 return aff;
1544 if (isl_int_is_one(aff->v->el[0])(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(aff->v->el[0]), 1) == 0))
1545 return aff;
1546
1547 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
1548 if (!aff)
1549 return NULL((void*)0);
1550
1551 aff->v = isl_vec_cow(aff->v);
1552 if (!aff->v)
1553 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1554
1555 if (isl_aff_is_cst(aff)) {
1556 isl_int_fdiv_q(aff->v->el[1], aff->v->el[1], aff->v->el[0])isl_sioimath_fdiv_q((aff->v->el[1]), *(aff->v->el
[1]), *(aff->v->el[0]));
1557 isl_int_set_si(aff->v->el[0], 1)isl_sioimath_set_si((aff->v->el[0]), 1);
1558 return aff;
1559 }
1560
1561 div = isl_vec_copy(aff->v);
1562 div = isl_vec_cow(div);
1563 if (!div)
1564 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1565
1566 ctx = isl_aff_get_ctx(aff);
1567 isl_int_fdiv_q(aff->v->el[0], aff->v->el[0], ctx->two)isl_sioimath_fdiv_q((aff->v->el[0]), *(aff->v->el
[0]), *(ctx->two));
1568 for (i = 1; i < aff->v->size; ++i) {
1569 isl_int_fdiv_r(div->el[i], div->el[i], div->el[0])isl_sioimath_fdiv_r((div->el[i]), *(div->el[i]), *(div->
el[0]));
1570 isl_int_fdiv_q(aff->v->el[i], aff->v->el[i], div->el[0])isl_sioimath_fdiv_q((aff->v->el[i]), *(aff->v->el
[i]), *(div->el[0]));
1571 if (isl_int_gt(div->el[i], aff->v->el[0])(isl_sioimath_cmp(*(div->el[i]), *(aff->v->el[0])) >
0)) {
1572 isl_int_sub(div->el[i], div->el[i], div->el[0])isl_sioimath_sub((div->el[i]), *(div->el[i]), *(div->
el[0]));
1573 isl_int_add_ui(aff->v->el[i], aff->v->el[i], 1)isl_sioimath_add_ui((aff->v->el[i]), *(aff->v->el
[i]), 1);
1574 }
1575 }
1576
1577 aff->ls = isl_local_space_add_div(aff->ls, div);
1578 if (!aff->ls)
1579 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1580
1581 size = aff->v->size;
1582 aff->v = isl_vec_extend(aff->v, size + 1);
1583 if (!aff->v)
1584 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1585 isl_int_set_si(aff->v->el[0], 1)isl_sioimath_set_si((aff->v->el[0]), 1);
1586 isl_int_set_si(aff->v->el[size], 1)isl_sioimath_set_si((aff->v->el[size]), 1);
1587
1588 aff = isl_aff_normalize(aff);
1589
1590 return aff;
1591}

1593/* Compute
1594 *
1595 * aff mod m = aff - m * floor(aff/m)
1596 */
1597__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_mod(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff, isl_int m)
1598{
1599 isl_aff *res;
1600
1601 res = isl_aff_copy(aff);
1602 aff = isl_aff_scale_down(aff, m);
1603 aff = isl_aff_floor(aff);
1604 aff = isl_aff_scale(aff, m);
1605 res = isl_aff_sub(res, aff);
1606
1607 return res;
1608}

1681/* Given f, return ceil(f).
1682 * If f is an integer expression, then just return f.
1683 * Otherwise, let f be the expression

1685 * e/m
1686 *
1687 * then return
1688 *
1689 * floor((e + m - 1)/m)

1693__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_ceil(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
1694{

1696 return NULL((void*)0);

1698 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff))
1699 return aff;
1700 if (isl_int_is_one(aff->v->el[0])(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(aff->v->el[0]), 1) == 0))
1701 return aff;
1702
1703 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
1704 if (!aff)
1705 return NULL((void*)0);

1707 if (!aff->v)
1708 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1709
1710 isl_int_add(aff->v->el[1], aff->v->el[1], aff->v->el[0])isl_sioimath_add((aff->v->el[1]), *(aff->v->el[1]
), *(aff->v->el[0]));
1711 isl_int_sub_ui(aff->v->el[1], aff->v->el[1], 1)isl_sioimath_sub_ui((aff->v->el[1]), *(aff->v->el
[1]), 1);
1712 aff = isl_aff_floor(aff);

1717/* Apply the expansion computed by isl_merge_divs.
1718 * The expansion itself is given by "exp" while the resulting
1719 * list of divs is given by "div".
1720 */
1721__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_expand_divs(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
1722 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_mat *div, int *exp)
1723{
1724 int old_n_div;
1725 int new_n_div;
1726 int offset;
1727
1728 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
1729 if (!aff || !div)
1730 goto error;
1731
1732 old_n_div = isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1733 new_n_div = isl_mat_rows(div);
1734 offset = 1 + isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
1735
1736 aff->v = isl_vec_expand(aff->v, offset, old_n_div, exp, new_n_div);
1737 aff->ls = isl_local_space_replace_divs(aff->ls, div);
1738 if (!aff->v || !aff->ls)
1739 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1740 return aff;
1741error:
1742 isl_aff_free(aff);
1743 isl_mat_free(div);
1744 return NULL((void*)0);
1745}

1747/* Add two affine expressions that live in the same local space.
1748 */
1749static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *add_expanded(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff1,
1750 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff2)
1751{
1752 isl_int gcd, f;
1753
1754 aff1 = isl_aff_cow(aff1);
1755 if (!aff1 || !aff2)
1756 goto error;
1757
1758 aff1->v = isl_vec_cow(aff1->v);
1759 if (!aff1->v)
1760 goto error;
1761
1762 isl_int_init(gcd)isl_sioimath_init((gcd));
1763 isl_int_init(f)isl_sioimath_init((f));
1764 isl_int_gcd(gcd, aff1->v->el[0], aff2->v->el[0])isl_sioimath_gcd((gcd), *(aff1->v->el[0]), *(aff2->v
->el[0]));
1765 isl_int_divexact(f, aff2->v->el[0], gcd)isl_sioimath_tdiv_q((f), *(aff2->v->el[0]), *(gcd));
1766 isl_seq_scale(aff1->v->el + 1, aff1->v->el + 1, f, aff1->v->size - 1);
1767 isl_int_divexact(f, aff1->v->el[0], gcd)isl_sioimath_tdiv_q((f), *(aff1->v->el[0]), *(gcd));
1768 isl_seq_addmul(aff1->v->el + 1, f, aff2->v->el + 1, aff1->v->size - 1);
1769 isl_int_divexact(f, aff2->v->el[0], gcd)isl_sioimath_tdiv_q((f), *(aff2->v->el[0]), *(gcd));
1770 isl_int_mul(aff1->v->el[0], aff1->v->el[0], f)isl_sioimath_mul((aff1->v->el[0]), *(aff1->v->el[
0]), *(f));
1771 isl_int_clear(f)isl_sioimath_clear((f));
1772 isl_int_clear(gcd)isl_sioimath_clear((gcd));
1773
1774 isl_aff_free(aff2);
1775 return aff1;
1776error:
1777 isl_aff_free(aff1);
1778 isl_aff_free(aff2);
1779 return NULL((void*)0);
1780}

1782/* Return the sum of "aff1" and "aff2".
1783 *
1784 * If either of the two is NaN, then the result is NaN.
1785 */
1786__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_add(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff1,
1787 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff2)
1788{
1789 isl_ctx *ctx;
1790 int *exp1 = NULL((void*)0);
1791 int *exp2 = NULL((void*)0);
1792 isl_mat *div;
1793 int n_div1, n_div2;
1794
1795 if (!aff1 || !aff2)
1796 goto error;
1797
1798 ctx = isl_aff_get_ctx(aff1);
1799 if (!isl_space_is_equal(aff1->ls->dim, aff2->ls->dim))
1800 isl_die(ctx, isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "spaces don't match"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 1801); goto error; } while (0)
1801 "spaces don't match", goto error)do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "spaces don't match"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 1801); goto error; } while (0);
1802
1803 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff1)) {
1804 isl_aff_free(aff2);
1805 return aff1;
1806 }
1807 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff2)) {
1808 isl_aff_free(aff1);
1809 return aff2;
1810 }
1811
1812 n_div1 = isl_aff_dim(aff1, isl_dim_div);
1813 n_div2 = isl_aff_dim(aff2, isl_dim_div);
1814 if (n_div1 == 0 && n_div2 == 0)
1815 return add_expanded(aff1, aff2);
1816
1817 exp1 = isl_alloc_array(ctx, int, n_div1)((int *)isl_malloc_or_die(ctx, (n_div1)*sizeof(int)));
1818 exp2 = isl_alloc_array(ctx, int, n_div2)((int *)isl_malloc_or_die(ctx, (n_div2)*sizeof(int)));
1819 if ((n_div1 && !exp1) || (n_div2 && !exp2))
1820 goto error;
1821
1822 div = isl_merge_divs(aff1->ls->div, aff2->ls->div, exp1, exp2);
1823 aff1 = isl_aff_expand_divs(aff1, isl_mat_copy(div), exp1);
1824 aff2 = isl_aff_expand_divs(aff2, div, exp2);
1825 free(exp1);
1826 free(exp2);
1827
1828 return add_expanded(aff1, aff2);
1829error:
1830 free(exp1);
1831 free(exp2);
1832 isl_aff_free(aff1);
1833 isl_aff_free(aff2);
1834 return NULL((void*)0);
1835}

1837__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_sub(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff1,
1838 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff2)
1839{

1843/* Return the result of scaling "aff" by a factor of "f".
1844 *
1845 * As a special case, f * NaN = NaN.
1846 */
1847__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_scale(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff, isl_int f)
1848{
1849 isl_int gcd;
1850
1851 if (!aff)
1852 return NULL((void*)0);
1853 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff))
1854 return aff;
1855
1856 if (isl_int_is_one(f)(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(f), 1) == 0))
1857 return aff;
1858
1859 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
1860 if (!aff)
1861 return NULL((void*)0);
1862 aff->v = isl_vec_cow(aff->v);
1863 if (!aff->v)
1864 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1865
1866 if (isl_int_is_pos(f)(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(f)) > 0) && isl_int_is_divisible_by(aff->v->el[0], f)isl_sioimath_is_divisible_by(*(aff->v->el[0]), *(f))) {
1867 isl_int_divexact(aff->v->el[0], aff->v->el[0], f)isl_sioimath_tdiv_q((aff->v->el[0]), *(aff->v->el
[0]), *(f));
1868 return aff;
1869 }
1870
1871 isl_int_init(gcd)isl_sioimath_init((gcd));
1872 isl_int_gcd(gcd, aff->v->el[0], f)isl_sioimath_gcd((gcd), *(aff->v->el[0]), *(f));
1873 isl_int_divexact(aff->v->el[0], aff->v->el[0], gcd)isl_sioimath_tdiv_q((aff->v->el[0]), *(aff->v->el
[0]), *(gcd));
1874 isl_int_divexact(gcd, f, gcd)isl_sioimath_tdiv_q((gcd), *(f), *(gcd));
1875 isl_seq_scale(aff->v->el + 1, aff->v->el + 1, gcd, aff->v->size - 1);
1876 isl_int_clear(gcd)isl_sioimath_clear((gcd));
1877
1878 return aff;
1879}

1909/* Return the result of scaling "aff" down by a factor of "f".
1910 *
1911 * As a special case, NaN/f = NaN.
1912 */
1913__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_scale_down(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff, isl_int f)
1914{
1915 isl_int gcd;
1916
1917 if (!aff)
1918 return NULL((void*)0);
1919 if (isl_aff_is_nan(aff))
1920 return aff;
1921
1922 if (isl_int_is_one(f)(isl_sioimath_cmp_si(*(f), 1) == 0))
1923 return aff;
1924
1925 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
1926 if (!aff)
1927 return NULL((void*)0);
1928
1929 if (isl_int_is_zero(f)(isl_sioimath_sgn(*(f)) == 0))
1930 isl_die(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "cannot scale down by zero", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 1931); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
1931 "cannot scale down by zero", return isl_aff_free(aff))do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "cannot scale down by zero", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 1931); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0);
1932
1933 aff->v = isl_vec_cow(aff->v);
1934 if (!aff->v)
1935 return isl_aff_free(aff);
1936
1937 isl_int_init(gcd)isl_sioimath_init((gcd));
1938 isl_seq_gcd(aff->v->el + 1, aff->v->size - 1, &gcd);
1939 isl_int_gcd(gcd, gcd, f)isl_sioimath_gcd((gcd), *(gcd), *(f));
1940 isl_seq_scale_down(aff->v->el + 1, aff->v->el + 1, gcd, aff->v->size - 1);
1941 isl_int_divexact(gcd, f, gcd)isl_sioimath_tdiv_q((gcd), *(f), *(gcd));
1942 isl_int_mul(aff->v->el[0], aff->v->el[0], gcd)isl_sioimath_mul((aff->v->el[0]), *(aff->v->el[0]
), *(gcd));
1943 isl_int_clear(gcd)isl_sioimath_clear((gcd));
1944
1945 return aff;
1946}

2059/* Exploit the equalities in "eq" to simplify the affine expression
2060 * and the expressions of the integer divisions in the local space.
2061 * The integer divisions in this local space are assumed to appear
2062 * as regular dimensions in "eq".
2063 */
2064static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_substitute_equalities_lifted(
2065 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *eq)
2066{
2067 int i, j;
2068 unsigned total;
2069 unsigned n_div;
2070
2071 if (!eq)
2072 goto error;
2073 if (eq->n_eq == 0) {
2074 isl_basic_set_free(eq);
2075 return aff;
2076 }
2077
2078 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
2079 if (!aff)
2080 goto error;
2081
2082 aff->ls = isl_local_space_substitute_equalities(aff->ls,
2083 isl_basic_set_copy(eq));
2084 aff->v = isl_vec_cow(aff->v);
2085 if (!aff->ls || !aff->v)
2086 goto error;
2087
2088 total = 1 + isl_space_dim(eq->dim, isl_dim_all);
2089 n_div = eq->n_div;
2090 for (i = 0; i < eq->n_eq; ++i) {
2091 j = isl_seq_last_non_zero(eq->eq[i], total + n_div);
2092 if (j < 0 || j == 0 || j >= total)
2093 continue;
2094
2095 isl_seq_elim(aff->v->el + 1, eq->eq[i], j, total,
2096 &aff->v->el[0]);
2097 }
2098
2099 isl_basic_set_free(eq);
2100 aff = isl_aff_normalize(aff);
2101 return aff;
2102error:
2103 isl_basic_set_free(eq);
2104 isl_aff_free(aff);
2105 return NULL((void*)0);
2106}
2107
2108/* Exploit the equalities in "eq" to simplify the affine expression
2109 * and the expressions of the integer divisions in the local space.
2110 */
2111__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_substitute_equalities(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
2112 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *eq)
2113{
2114 int n_div;
2115
2116 if (!aff || !eq)
2117 goto error;
2118 n_div = isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
2119 if (n_div > 0)
2120 eq = isl_basic_set_add_dims(eq, isl_dim_set, n_div);
2121 return isl_aff_substitute_equalities_lifted(aff, eq);
2122error:
2123 isl_basic_set_free(eq);
2124 isl_aff_free(aff);
2125 return NULL((void*)0);
2126}

2128/* Look for equalities among the variables shared by context and aff
2129 * and the integer divisions of aff, if any.
2130 * The equalities are then used to eliminate coefficients and/or integer
2131 * divisions from aff.
2132 */
2133__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_gist(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
2134 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_setisl_map *context)
2135{
2136 isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *hull;
2137 int n_div;
2138
2139 if (!aff)
2140 goto error;
2141 n_div = isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, isl_dim_div);
2142 if (n_div > 0) {
2143 isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset;
2144 isl_local_space *ls;
2145 context = isl_set_add_dims(context, isl_dim_set, n_div);
2146 ls = isl_aff_get_domain_local_space(aff);
2147 bset = isl_basic_set_from_local_space(ls);
2148 bset = isl_basic_set_lift(bset);
2149 bset = isl_basic_set_flatten(bset);
2150 context = isl_set_intersect(context,
2151 isl_set_from_basic_set(bset));
2152 }
2153
2154 hull = isl_set_affine_hull(context);
2155 return isl_aff_substitute_equalities_lifted(aff, hull);
2156error:
2157 isl_aff_free(aff);
2158 isl_set_free(context);
2159 return NULL((void*)0);
2160}

2162__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_gist_params(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
2163 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_setisl_map *context)
2164{
2165 isl_setisl_map *dom_context = isl_set_universe(isl_aff_get_domain_space(aff));
2166 dom_context = isl_set_intersect_params(dom_context, context);
2167 return isl_aff_gist(aff, dom_context);
2168}

2170/* Return a basic set containing those elements in the space

2173 * If "aff" is NaN, then it is not positive.

2175static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *aff_pos_basic_set(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
2176 int rational)
2177{
2178 isl_constraint *ineq;
2179 isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset;

2182 if (!aff)
2183 return NULL((void*)0);

2185 isl_space *space = isl_aff_get_domain_space(aff);
2186 isl_aff_free(aff);

2190 isl_die(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_unsupported,do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_unsupported
, "rational sets not supported", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"

, 2191); goto error; } while (0);

2194 c = isl_constraint_get_constant_val(ineq);
2195 c = isl_val_sub_ui(c, 1);
2196 ineq = isl_constraint_set_constant_val(ineq, c);
2197
2198 bset = isl_basic_set_from_constraint(ineq);
2199 bset = isl_basic_set_simplify(bset);

2201error:

2313__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *isl_aff_le_basic_set(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff1,
2314 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff2)
2315{
2316 return isl_aff_ge_basic_set(aff2, aff1);
2317}
2318
2319/* Return a set containing those elements in the shared space
2320 * of aff1 and aff2 where aff1 is smaller than or equal to aff2.
2321 */
2322__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *isl_aff_le_set(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff1,
2323 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff2)
2324{
2325 return isl_aff_ge_set(aff2, aff1);
2326}
2327
2328/* Return a basic set containing those elements in the shared space
2329 * of aff1 and aff2 where aff1 and aff2 are equal.
2330 */
2331__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *isl_aff_eq_basic_set(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff1,
2332 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff2)
2333{
2334 aff1 = isl_aff_sub(aff1, aff2);
2335
2336 return isl_aff_zero_basic_set(aff1);
2337}
2338
2339/* Return a set containing those elements in the shared space
2340 * of aff1 and aff2 where aff1 and aff2 are equal.
2341 */
2342__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *isl_aff_eq_set(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff1,
2343 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff2)
2344{
2345 return isl_set_from_basic_set(isl_aff_eq_basic_set(aff1, aff2));
2346}

2348__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_add_on_domain(__isl_keep isl_setisl_map *dom,
2349 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff2)

2364/* Check whether the given affine expression has non-zero coefficient
2365 * for any dimension in the given range or if any of these dimensions
2366 * appear with non-zero coefficients in any of the integer divisions
2367 * involved in the affine expression.
2368 */
2369isl_bool isl_aff_involves_dims(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff,
2370 enum isl_dim_type type, unsigned first, unsigned n)
2371{
2372 int i;
2373 isl_ctx *ctx;
2374 int *active = NULL((void*)0);
2375 isl_bool involves = isl_bool_false;
2376
2377 if (!aff)
2378 return isl_bool_error;
2379 if (n == 0)
2380 return isl_bool_false;
2381
2382 ctx = isl_aff_get_ctx(aff);
2383 if (first + n > isl_aff_dim(aff, type))
2384 isl_die(ctx, isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "range out of bounds"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2385); return isl_bool_error; } while (0)
2385 "range out of bounds", return isl_bool_error)do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "range out of bounds"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2385); return isl_bool_error; } while (0);
2386
2387 active = isl_local_space_get_active(aff->ls, aff->v->el + 2);
2388 if (!active)
2389 goto error;
2390
2391 first += isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, type) - 1;
2392 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i)
2393 if (active[first + i]) {
2394 involves = isl_bool_true;
2395 break;
2396 }
2397
2398 free(active);
2399
2400 return involves;
2401error:
2402 free(active);
2403 return isl_bool_error;
2404}

2406__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_drop_dims(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
2407 enum isl_dim_type type, unsigned first, unsigned n)
2408{
2409 isl_ctx *ctx;
2410
2411 if (!aff)
2412 return NULL((void*)0);
2413 if (type == isl_dim_out)
2414 isl_die(aff->v->ctx, isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(aff->v->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "cannot drop output/set dimension"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2416); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2415 "cannot drop output/set dimension",do { isl_handle_error(aff->v->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "cannot drop output/set dimension"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2416); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2416 return isl_aff_free(aff))do { isl_handle_error(aff->v->ctx, isl_error_invalid, "cannot drop output/set dimension"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2416); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0);
2417 if (type == isl_dim_in)
2418 type = isl_dim_set;
2419 if (n == 0 && !isl_local_space_is_named_or_nested(aff->ls, type))
2420 return aff;
2421
2422 ctx = isl_aff_get_ctx(aff);
2423 if (first + n > isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, type))
2424 isl_die(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "range out of bounds",do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "range out of bounds"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2425); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2425 return isl_aff_free(aff))do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "range out of bounds"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2425); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0);
2426
2427 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
2428 if (!aff)
2429 return NULL((void*)0);
2430
2431 aff->ls = isl_local_space_drop_dims(aff->ls, type, first, n);
2432 if (!aff->ls)
2433 return isl_aff_free(aff);
2434
2435 first += 1 + isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, type);
2436 aff->v = isl_vec_drop_els(aff->v, first, n);
2437 if (!aff->v)
2438 return isl_aff_free(aff);
2439
2440 return aff;
2441}

2443/* Project the domain of the affine expression onto its parameter space.
2444 * The affine expression may not involve any of the domain dimensions.
2445 */
2446__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_project_domain_on_params(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff)
2447{
2448 isl_space *space;
2449 unsigned n;
2450 int involves;
2451
2452 n = isl_aff_dim(aff, isl_dim_in);
2453 involves = isl_aff_involves_dims(aff, isl_dim_in, 0, n);
2454 if (involves < 0)
2455 return isl_aff_free(aff);
2456 if (involves)
2457 isl_die(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "affine expression involves some of the domain dimensions",
"/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2459); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2458 "affine expression involves some of the domain dimensions",do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "affine expression involves some of the domain dimensions",
"/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2459); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2459 return isl_aff_free(aff))do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "affine expression involves some of the domain dimensions",
"/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2459); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0);
2460 aff = isl_aff_drop_dims(aff, isl_dim_in, 0, n);
2461 space = isl_aff_get_domain_space(aff);
2462 space = isl_space_params(space);
2463 aff = isl_aff_reset_domain_space(aff, space);
2464 return aff;
2465}

, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"

2524/* Move the "n" dimensions of "src_type" starting at "src_pos" of "aff"
2525 * to dimensions of "dst_type" at "dst_pos".
2526 *
2527 * We only support moving input dimensions to parameters and vice versa.
2528 */
2529__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_aff *isl_aff_move_dims(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff,
2530 enum isl_dim_type dst_type, unsigned dst_pos,
2531 enum isl_dim_type src_type, unsigned src_pos, unsigned n)
2532{
2533 unsigned g_dst_pos;
2534 unsigned g_src_pos;
2535
2536 if (!aff)
2537 return NULL((void*)0);
2538 if (n == 0 &&
2539 !isl_local_space_is_named_or_nested(aff->ls, src_type) &&
2540 !isl_local_space_is_named_or_nested(aff->ls, dst_type))
2541 return aff;
2542
2543 if (dst_type == isl_dim_out || src_type == isl_dim_out)
2544 isl_die(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "cannot move output/set dimension", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2546); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2545 "cannot move output/set dimension",do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "cannot move output/set dimension", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2546); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2546 return isl_aff_free(aff))do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "cannot move output/set dimension", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2546); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0);
2547 if (dst_type == isl_dim_div || src_type == isl_dim_div)
2548 isl_die(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "cannot move divs", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2549); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2549 "cannot move divs", return isl_aff_free(aff))do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "cannot move divs", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2549); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0);
2550 if (dst_type == isl_dim_in)
2551 dst_type = isl_dim_set;
2552 if (src_type == isl_dim_in)
2553 src_type = isl_dim_set;
2554
2555 if (src_pos + n > isl_local_space_dim(aff->ls, src_type))
2556 isl_die(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "range out of bounds", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2557); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2557 "range out of bounds", return isl_aff_free(aff))do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_invalid
, "range out of bounds", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2557); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0);
2558 if (dst_type == src_type)
2559 isl_die(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_unsupported,do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_unsupported
, "moving dims within the same type not supported", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2561); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2560 "moving dims within the same type not supported",do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_unsupported
, "moving dims within the same type not supported", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2561); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0)
2561 return isl_aff_free(aff))do { isl_handle_error(isl_aff_get_ctx(aff), isl_error_unsupported
, "moving dims within the same type not supported", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2561); return isl_aff_free(aff); } while (0);
2562
2563 aff = isl_aff_cow(aff);
2564 if (!aff)
2565 return NULL((void*)0);
2566
2567 g_src_pos = 1 + isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, src_type) + src_pos;
2568 g_dst_pos = 1 + isl_local_space_offset(aff->ls, dst_type) + dst_pos;
2569 if (dst_type > src_type)
2570 g_dst_pos -= n;
2571
2572 aff->v = isl_vec_move_els(aff->v, g_dst_pos, g_src_pos, n);
2573 aff->ls = isl_local_space_move_dims(aff->ls, dst_type, dst_pos,
2574 src_type, src_pos, n);
2575 if (!aff->v || !aff->ls)
2576 return isl_aff_free(aff);
2577
2578 aff = sort_divs(aff);
2579
2580 return aff;
2581}

2623static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *align_params_pw_pw_set_and(
2624 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2,
2625 __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *(*fn)(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
2626 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2))
2627{
2628 if (!pwaff1 || !pwaff2)
2629 goto error;

2631 pwaff2->dim, isl_dim_param))
2632 return fn(pwaff1, pwaff2);
2633 if (!isl_space_has_named_params(pwaff1->dim) ||
2634 !isl_space_has_named_params(pwaff2->dim))
2635 isl_die(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pwaff1), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pwaff1), isl_error_invalid
, "unaligned unnamed parameters", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2636); goto error; } while (0)
2636 "unaligned unnamed parameters", goto error)do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pwaff1), isl_error_invalid
, "unaligned unnamed parameters", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2636); goto error; } while (0);
2637 pwaff1 = isl_pw_aff_align_params(pwaff1, isl_pw_aff_get_space(pwaff2));
2638 pwaff2 = isl_pw_aff_align_params(pwaff2, isl_pw_aff_get_space(pwaff1));
2639 return fn(pwaff1, pwaff2);
2640error:
2641 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff1);
2642 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff2);
2643 return NULL((void*)0);
2644}

2646/* Align the parameters of the to isl_pw_aff arguments and
2647 * then apply a function "fn" on them that returns an isl_map.
2648 */
2649static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *align_params_pw_pw_map_and(
2650 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa2,
2651 __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *(*fn)(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa1,
2652 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa2))
2653{

2657 return fn(pa1, pa2);
2658 if (!isl_space_has_named_params(pa1->dim) ||
2659 !isl_space_has_named_params(pa2->dim))
2660 isl_die(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa1), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa1), isl_error_invalid
, "unaligned unnamed parameters", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2661); goto error; } while (0)
2661 "unaligned unnamed parameters", goto error)do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa1), isl_error_invalid
, "unaligned unnamed parameters", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2661); goto error; } while (0);
2662 pa1 = isl_pw_aff_align_params(pa1, isl_pw_aff_get_space(pa2));
2663 pa2 = isl_pw_aff_align_params(pa2, isl_pw_aff_get_space(pa1));
2664 return fn(pa1, pa2);
2665error:
2666 isl_pw_aff_free(pa1);
2667 isl_pw_aff_free(pa2);
2668 return NULL((void*)0);
2669}

2671/* Compute a piecewise quasi-affine expression with a domain that
2672 * is the union of those of pwaff1 and pwaff2 and such that on each
2673 * cell, the quasi-affine expression is the maximum of those of pwaff1
2674 * and pwaff2. If only one of pwaff1 or pwaff2 is defined on a given
2675 * cell, then the associated expression is the defined one.
2676 */
2677static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *pw_aff_union_max(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
2678 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2)
2679{
2680 return isl_pw_aff_union_opt_cmp(pwaff1, pwaff2, &isl_aff_ge_set);
2681}
2682
2683__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *isl_pw_aff_union_max(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
2684 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2)
2685{
2686 return isl_pw_aff_align_params_pw_pw_and(pwaff1, pwaff2,
2687 &pw_aff_union_max);
2688}

2690/* Compute a piecewise quasi-affine expression with a domain that
2691 * is the union of those of pwaff1 and pwaff2 and such that on each
2692 * cell, the quasi-affine expression is the minimum of those of pwaff1
2693 * and pwaff2. If only one of pwaff1 or pwaff2 is defined on a given
2694 * cell, then the associated expression is the defined one.
2695 */
2696static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *pw_aff_union_min(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
2697 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2)
2698{
2699 return isl_pw_aff_union_opt_cmp(pwaff1, pwaff2, &isl_aff_le_set);
2700}
2701
2702__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *isl_pw_aff_union_min(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
2703 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2)
2704{
2705 return isl_pw_aff_align_params_pw_pw_and(pwaff1, pwaff2,
2706 &pw_aff_union_min);
2707}
2708
2709__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *isl_pw_aff_union_opt(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
2710 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2, int max)
2711{
2712 if (max)
2713 return isl_pw_aff_union_max(pwaff1, pwaff2);
2714 else
2715 return isl_pw_aff_union_min(pwaff1, pwaff2);
2716}

2718/* Construct a map with as domain the domain of pwaff and
2719 * one-dimensional range corresponding to the affine expressions.
2720 */
2721static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *map_from_pw_aff(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff)
2722{
2723 int i;
2724 isl_space *dim;
2725 isl_map *map;
2726
2727 if (!pwaff)
2728 return NULL((void*)0);
2729
2730 dim = isl_pw_aff_get_space(pwaff);
2731 map = isl_map_empty(dim);
2732
2733 for (i = 0; i < pwaff->n; ++i) {
2734 isl_basic_map *bmap;
2735 isl_map *map_i;
2736
2737 bmap = isl_basic_map_from_aff(isl_aff_copy(pwaff->p[i].aff));
2738 map_i = isl_map_from_basic_map(bmap);
2739 map_i = isl_map_intersect_domain(map_i,
2740 isl_set_copy(pwaff->p[i].set));
2741 map = isl_map_union_disjoint(map, map_i);
2742 }
2743
2744 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff);
2745
2746 return map;
2747}

, "space of input is not a map", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 2758); goto error; } while (0)

, "space of input is not a map", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"

2782/* Return a set containing those elements in the domain
2783 * of "pwaff" where it satisfies "fn" (if complement is 0) or
2784 * does not satisfy "fn" (if complement is 1).
2785 *
2786 * The pieces with a NaN never belong to the result since
2787 * NaN does not satisfy any property.
2788 */
2789static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *pw_aff_locus(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff,
2790 __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *(*fn)(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_aff *aff, int rational),
2791 int complement)
2792{
2793 int i;
2794 isl_setisl_map *set;
2795
2796 if (!pwaff)
2797 return NULL((void*)0);
2798
2799 set = isl_set_empty(isl_pw_aff_get_domain_space(pwaff));
2800
2801 for (i = 0; i < pwaff->n; ++i) {
2802 isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *bset;
2803 isl_setisl_map *set_i, *locus;
2804 int rational;
2805
2806 if (isl_aff_is_nan(pwaff->p[i].aff))
2807 continue;
2808
2809 rational = isl_set_has_rational(pwaff->p[i].set);
2810 bset = fn(isl_aff_copy(pwaff->p[i].aff), rational);
2811 locus = isl_set_from_basic_set(bset);
2812 set_i = isl_set_copy(pwaff->p[i].set);
2813 if (complement)
2814 set_i = isl_set_subtract(set_i, locus);
2815 else
2816 set_i = isl_set_intersect(set_i, locus);
2817 set = isl_set_union_disjoint(set, set_i);
2818 }
2819
2820 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff);
2821
2822 return set;
2823}

2857/* Return a set containing those elements in the shared domain
2858 * of pwaff1 and pwaff2 where pwaff1 is greater than (or equal) to pwaff2.
2859 *
2860 * We compute the difference on the shared domain and then construct
2861 * the set of values where this difference is non-negative.
2862 * If strict is set, we first subtract 1 from the difference.
2863 * If equal is set, we only return the elements where pwaff1 and pwaff2
2864 * are equal.
2865 */
2866static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *pw_aff_gte_set(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
2867 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2, int strict, int equal)
2868{
2869 isl_setisl_map *set1, *set2;
2870
2871 set1 = isl_pw_aff_domain(isl_pw_aff_copy(pwaff1));
2872 set2 = isl_pw_aff_domain(isl_pw_aff_copy(pwaff2));
2873 set1 = isl_set_intersect(set1, set2);
2874 pwaff1 = isl_pw_aff_intersect_domain(pwaff1, isl_set_copy(set1));
2875 pwaff2 = isl_pw_aff_intersect_domain(pwaff2, isl_set_copy(set1));
2876 pwaff1 = isl_pw_aff_add(pwaff1, isl_pw_aff_neg(pwaff2));
2877
2878 if (strict) {
2879 isl_space *dim = isl_set_get_space(set1);
2880 isl_aff *aff;
2881 aff = isl_aff_zero_on_domain(isl_local_space_from_space(dim));
2882 aff = isl_aff_add_constant_si(aff, -1);
2883 pwaff1 = isl_pw_aff_add(pwaff1, isl_pw_aff_alloc(set1, aff));
2884 } else
2885 isl_set_free(set1);
2886
2887 if (equal)
2888 return isl_pw_aff_zero_set(pwaff1);
2889 return isl_pw_aff_nonneg_set(pwaff1);
2890}

2949/* Return a map containing pairs of elements in the domains of "pa1" and "pa2"
2950 * where the function values are ordered in the same way as "order",
2951 * which returns a set in the shared domain of its two arguments.
2952 * The parameters of "pa1" and "pa2" are assumed to have been aligned.
2953 *
2954 * Let "pa1" and "pa2" be defined on domains A and B respectively.
2955 * We first pull back the two functions such that they are defined on
2956 * the domain [A -> B]. Then we apply "order", resulting in a set
2957 * in the space [A -> B]. Finally, we unwrap this set to obtain
2958 * a map in the space A -> B.
2959 */
2960static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *isl_pw_aff_order_map_aligned(
2961 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa2,
2962 __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *(*order)(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa1,
2963 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa2))
2964{
2965 isl_space *space1, *space2;
2966 isl_multi_aff *ma;
2967 isl_setisl_map *set;
2968
2969 space1 = isl_space_domain(isl_pw_aff_get_space(pa1));
2970 space2 = isl_space_domain(isl_pw_aff_get_space(pa2));
2971 space1 = isl_space_map_from_domain_and_range(space1, space2);
2972 ma = isl_multi_aff_domain_map(isl_space_copy(space1));
2973 pa1 = isl_pw_aff_pullback_multi_aff(pa1, ma);
2974 ma = isl_multi_aff_range_map(space1);
2975 pa2 = isl_pw_aff_pullback_multi_aff(pa2, ma);
2976 set = order(pa1, pa2);
2977
2978 return isl_set_unwrap(set);
2979}

3040/* Return a set containing those elements in the shared domain
3041 * of the elements of list1 and list2 where each element in list1
3042 * has the relation specified by "fn" with each element in list2.
3043 */
3044static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *pw_aff_list_set(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff_list *list1,
3045 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff_list *list2,
3046 __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *(*fn)(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
3047 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2))
3048{
3049 int i, j;
3050 isl_ctx *ctx;
3051 isl_setisl_map *set;
3052
3053 if (!list1 || !list2)
3054 goto error;
3055
3056 ctx = isl_pw_aff_list_get_ctx(list1);
3057 if (list1->n < 1 || list2->n < 1)
3058 isl_die(ctx, isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "list should contain at least one element"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 3059); goto error; } while (0)
3059 "list should contain at least one element", goto error)do { isl_handle_error(ctx, isl_error_invalid, "list should contain at least one element"
, "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 3059); goto error; } while (0);
3060
3061 set = isl_set_universe(isl_pw_aff_get_domain_space(list1->p[0]));
3062 for (i = 0; i < list1->n; ++i)
3063 for (j = 0; j < list2->n; ++j) {
3064 isl_setisl_map *set_ij;
3065
3066 set_ij = fn(isl_pw_aff_copy(list1->p[i]),
3067 isl_pw_aff_copy(list2->p[j]));
3068 set = isl_set_intersect(set, set_ij);
3069 }
3070
3071 isl_pw_aff_list_free(list1);
3072 isl_pw_aff_list_free(list2);
3073 return set;
3074error:
3075 isl_pw_aff_list_free(list1);
3076 isl_pw_aff_list_free(list2);
3077 return NULL((void*)0);
3078}

3209/* Assuming that "cond1" and "cond2" are disjoint,
3210 * return an affine expression that is equal to pwaff1 on cond1
3211 * and to pwaff2 on cond2.
3212 */
3213static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *isl_pw_aff_select(
3214 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_setisl_map *cond1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
3215 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_setisl_map *cond2, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2)
3216{
3217 pwaff1 = isl_pw_aff_intersect_domain(pwaff1, cond1);
3218 pwaff2 = isl_pw_aff_intersect_domain(pwaff2, cond2);
3219
3220 return isl_pw_aff_add_disjoint(pwaff1, pwaff2);
3221}
3222
3223/* Return an affine expression that is equal to pwaff_true for elements
3224 * where "cond" is non-zero and to pwaff_false for elements where "cond"
3225 * is zero.
3226 * That is, return cond ? pwaff_true : pwaff_false;
3227 *
3228 * If "cond" involves and NaN, then we conservatively return a NaN
3229 * on its entire domain. In principle, we could consider the pieces
3230 * where it is NaN separately from those where it is not.
3231 *
3232 * If "pwaff_true" and "pwaff_false" are obviously equal to each other,
3233 * then only use the domain of "cond" to restrict the domain.
3234 */
3235__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *isl_pw_aff_cond(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *cond,
3236 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff_true, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff_false)
3237{
3238 isl_setisl_map *cond_true, *cond_false;
3239 isl_bool equal;
3240
3241 if (!cond)
3242 goto error;
3243 if (isl_pw_aff_involves_nan(cond)) {
3244 isl_space *space = isl_pw_aff_get_domain_space(cond);
3245 isl_local_space *ls = isl_local_space_from_space(space);
3246 isl_pw_aff_free(cond);
3247 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff_true);
3248 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff_false);
3249 return isl_pw_aff_nan_on_domain(ls);
3250 }
3251
3252 pwaff_true = isl_pw_aff_align_params(pwaff_true,
3253 isl_pw_aff_get_space(pwaff_false));
3254 pwaff_false = isl_pw_aff_align_params(pwaff_false,
3255 isl_pw_aff_get_space(pwaff_true));
3256 equal = isl_pw_aff_plain_is_equal(pwaff_true, pwaff_false);
3257 if (equal < 0)
3258 goto error;
3259 if (equal) {
3260 isl_setisl_map *dom;
3261
3262 dom = isl_set_coalesce(isl_pw_aff_domain(cond));
3263 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff_false);
3264 return isl_pw_aff_intersect_domain(pwaff_true, dom);
3265 }
3266
3267 cond_true = isl_pw_aff_non_zero_set(isl_pw_aff_copy(cond));
3268 cond_false = isl_pw_aff_zero_set(cond);
3269 return isl_pw_aff_select(cond_true, pwaff_true,
3270 cond_false, pwaff_false);
3271error:
3272 isl_pw_aff_free(cond);
3273 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff_true);
3274 isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff_false);
3275 return NULL((void*)0);
3276}

3281 return isl_bool_error;
3282
3283 return isl_seq_first_non_zero(aff->v->el + 2, aff->v->size - 2) == -1;
3284}

3477/* Compute the quotient of the integer division of "pa1" by "pa2"
3478 * with rounding towards zero.
3479 * "pa2" is assumed to be a piecewise constant.
3480 *
3481 * In particular, return
3482 *
3483 * pa1 >= 0 ? floor(pa1/pa2) : ceil(pa1/pa2)
3484 *
3485 */
3486__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *isl_pw_aff_tdiv_q(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa1,
3487 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa2)
3488{
3489 int is_cst;
3490 isl_setisl_map *cond;
3491 isl_pw_aff *f, *c;
3492
3493 is_cst = isl_pw_aff_is_cst(pa2);
3494 if (is_cst < 0)
3495 goto error;
3496 if (!is_cst)
3497 isl_die(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa2), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa2), isl_error_invalid
, "second argument should be a piecewise constant", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 3499); goto error; } while (0)
3498 "second argument should be a piecewise constant",do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa2), isl_error_invalid
, "second argument should be a piecewise constant", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 3499); goto error; } while (0)
3499 goto error)do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa2), isl_error_invalid
, "second argument should be a piecewise constant", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 3499); goto error; } while (0);
3500
3501 pa1 = isl_pw_aff_div(pa1, pa2);
3502
3503 cond = isl_pw_aff_nonneg_set(isl_pw_aff_copy(pa1));
3504 f = isl_pw_aff_floor(isl_pw_aff_copy(pa1));
3505 c = isl_pw_aff_ceil(pa1);

3507error:

3513/* Compute the remainder of the integer division of "pa1" by "pa2"
3514 * with rounding towards zero.
3515 * "pa2" is assumed to be a piecewise constant.

3517 * In particular, return
3518 *
3519 * pa1 - pa2 * (pa1 >= 0 ? floor(pa1/pa2) : ceil(pa1/pa2))

3521 */
3522__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *isl_pw_aff_tdiv_r(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa1,
3523 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pa2)
3524{
3525 int is_cst;
3526 isl_pw_aff *res;
3527
3528 is_cst = isl_pw_aff_is_cst(pa2);
3529 if (is_cst < 0)
3530 goto error;
3531 if (!is_cst)
3532 isl_die(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa2), isl_error_invalid,do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa2), isl_error_invalid
, "second argument should be a piecewise constant", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 3534); goto error; } while (0)
3533 "second argument should be a piecewise constant",do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa2), isl_error_invalid
, "second argument should be a piecewise constant", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 3534); goto error; } while (0)
3534 goto error)do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_aff_get_ctx(pa2), isl_error_invalid
, "second argument should be a piecewise constant", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"
, 3534); goto error; } while (0);
3535 res = isl_pw_aff_tdiv_q(isl_pw_aff_copy(pa1), isl_pw_aff_copy(pa2));
3536 res = isl_pw_aff_mul(pa2, res);
3537 res = isl_pw_aff_sub(pa1, res);
3538 return res;
3539error:
3540 isl_pw_aff_free(pa1);
3541 isl_pw_aff_free(pa2);
3542 return NULL((void*)0);

3545static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *pw_aff_min(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff1,
3546 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff2)
3547{
3548 isl_setisl_map *le;
3549 isl_setisl_map *dom;
3550
3551 dom = isl_set_intersect(isl_pw_aff_domain(isl_pw_aff_copy(pwaff1)),
3552 isl_pw_aff_domain(isl_pw_aff_copy(pwaff2)));
3553 le = isl_pw_aff_le_set(isl_pw_aff_copy(pwaff1),
3554 isl_pw_aff_copy(pwaff2));
3555 dom = isl_set_subtract(dom, isl_set_copy(le));
3556 return isl_pw_aff_select(le, pwaff1, dom, pwaff2);
3557}

3631/* Mark the domains of "pwaff" as rational.
3632 */
3633__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff *isl_pw_aff_set_rational(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff *pwaff)
3634{
3635 int i;
3636
3637 pwaff = isl_pw_aff_cow(pwaff);
3638 if (!pwaff)
3639 return NULL((void*)0);
3640 if (pwaff->n == 0)
3641 return pwaff;
3642
3643 for (i = 0; i < pwaff->n; ++i) {
3644 pwaff->p[i].set = isl_set_set_rational(pwaff->p[i].set);
3645 if (!pwaff->p[i].set)
3646 return isl_pw_aff_free(pwaff);
3647 }
3648
3649 return pwaff;
3650}

3652/* Mark the domains of the elements of "list" as rational.
3653 */
3654__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_aff_list *isl_pw_aff_list_set_rational(
3655 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_aff_list *list)
3656{
3657 int i, n;
3658
3659 if (!list)
3660 return NULL((void*)0);
3661 if (list->n == 0)
3662 return list;
3663
3664 n = list->n;
3665 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
3666 isl_pw_aff *pa;
3667
3668 pa = isl_pw_aff_list_get_pw_aff(list, i);
3669 pa = isl_pw_aff_set_rational(pa);
3670 list = isl_pw_aff_list_set_pw_aff(list, i, pa);
3671 }
3672
3673 return list;
3674}

3676/* Do the parameters of "aff" match those of "space"?
3677 */
3678int isl_aff_matching_params(__isl_keep isl_aff *aff,
3679 __isl_keep isl_space *space)
3680{
3681 isl_space *aff_space;
3682 int match;
3683
3684 if (!aff || !space)
3685 return -1;
3686
3687 aff_space = isl_aff_get_domain_space(aff);
3688
3689 match = isl_space_match(space, isl_dim_param, aff_space, isl_dim_param);
3690
3691 isl_space_free(aff_space);
3692 return match;
3693}

3744/* Remove any internal structure of the domain of "ma".
3745 * If there is any such internal structure in the input,
3746 * then the name of the corresponding space is also removed.
3747 */
3748__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_multi_aff *isl_multi_aff_flatten_domain(
3749 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_multi_aff *ma)

3760 space = isl_space_flatten_domain(space);
3761 ma = isl_multi_aff_reset_space(ma, space);
3762
3763 return ma;

, "expecting set space", "/cluster/home/tgrosser/polly/llvm_git/tools/polly/lib/External/isl/isl_aff.c"

3946/* Exploit the equalities in "eq" to simplify the affine expressions.
3947 */
3948static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_multi_aff *isl_multi_aff_substitute_equalities(
3949 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_multi_aff *maff, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_basic_setisl_basic_map *eq)
3950{
3951 int i;
3952
3953 maff = isl_multi_aff_cow(maff);
3954 if (!maff || !eq)
3955 goto error;
3956
3957 for (i = 0; i < maff->n; ++i) {
3958 maff->p[i] = isl_aff_substitute_equalities(maff->p[i],
3959 isl_basic_set_copy(eq));
3960 if (!maff->p[i])
3961 goto error;
3962 }
3963
3964 isl_basic_set_free(eq);
3965 return maff;
3966error:
3967 isl_basic_set_free(eq);
3968 isl_multi_aff_free(maff);
3969 return NULL((void*)0);
3970}

3972__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_multi_aff *isl_multi_aff_scale(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_multi_aff *maff,
3973 isl_int f)

3975 int i;
3976
3977 maff = isl_multi_aff_cow(maff);

3982 maff->p[i] = isl_aff_scale(maff->p[i], f);

3984 return isl_multi_aff_free(maff);
3985 }

3987 return maff;
3988}

3995 return maff1;

4024/* Return the set of domain elements where "ma1" and "ma2"
4025 * satisfy "order".
4026 */
4027static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_setisl_map *isl_multi_aff_order_set(
4028 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_multi_aff *ma1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_multi_aff *ma2,
4029 __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *order(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_space *set_space))
4030{
4031 isl_space *space;
4032 isl_map *map1, *map2;
4033 isl_map *map, *ge;
4034
4035 map1 = isl_map_from_multi_aff(ma1);
4036 map2 = isl_map_from_multi_aff(ma2);
4037 map = isl_map_range_product(map1, map2);
4038 space = isl_space_range(isl_map_get_space(map));
4039 space = isl_space_domain(isl_space_unwrap(space));
4040 ge = order(space);
4041 map = isl_map_intersect_range(map, isl_map_wrap(ge));
4042
4043 return isl_map_domain(map);
4044}

4203/* Given two piecewise multi-affine expressions A -> B and C -> D,
4204 * construct a piecewise multi-affine expression [A -> C] -> [B -> D].
4205 */
4206static __isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_multi_aff *pw_multi_aff_product(
4207 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_multi_aff *pma1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_multi_aff *pma2)
4208{
4209 int i, j, n;
4210 isl_space *space;
4211 isl_pw_multi_aff *res;
4212
4213 if (!pma1 || !pma2)
4214 goto error;
4215
4216 n = pma1->n * pma2->n;
4217 space = isl_space_product(isl_space_copy(pma1->dim),
4218 isl_space_copy(pma2->dim));
4219 res = isl_pw_multi_aff_alloc_size(space, n);
4220
4221 for (i = 0; i < pma1->n; ++i) {
4222 for (j = 0; j < pma2->n; ++j) {
4223 isl_setisl_map *domain;
4224 isl_multi_aff *ma;
4225
4226 domain = isl_set_product(isl_set_copy(pma1->p[i].set),
4227 isl_set_copy(pma2->p[j].set));
4228 ma = isl_multi_aff_product(
4229 isl_multi_aff_copy(pma1->p[i].maff),
4230 isl_multi_aff_copy(pma2->p[j].maff));
4231 res = isl_pw_multi_aff_add_piece(res, domain, ma);
4232 }
4233 }
4234
4235 isl_pw_multi_aff_free(pma1);
4236 isl_pw_multi_aff_free(pma2);
4237 return res;
4238error:
4239 isl_pw_multi_aff_free(pma1);
4240 isl_pw_multi_aff_free(pma2);
4241 return NULL((void*)0);
4242}

4244__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_pw_multi_aff *isl_pw_multi_aff_product(
4245 __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_multi_aff *pma1, __isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_multi_aff *pma2)
4246{
4247 return isl_pw_multi_aff_align_params_pw_pw_and(pma1, pma2,
4248 &pw_multi_aff_product);
4249}

4251/* Construct a map mapping the domain of the piecewise multi-affine expression
4252 * to its range, with each dimension in the range equated to the
4253 * corresponding affine expression on its cell.
4254 */
4255__isl_give__attribute__((cf_returns_retained)) isl_map *isl_map_from_pw_multi_aff(__isl_take__attribute__((cf_consumed)) isl_pw_multi_aff *pma)
4256{
4257 int i;
4258 isl_map *map;
4259
4260 if (!pma)
4261 return NULL((void*)0);
4262
4263 map = isl_map_empty(isl_pw_multi_aff_get_space(pma));
4264
4265 for (i = 0; i < pma->n; ++i) {
4266 isl_multi_aff *maff;
4267 isl_basic_map *bmap;
4268 isl_map *map_i;
4269
4270 maff = isl_multi_aff_copy(pma->p[i].maff);
4271 bmap = isl_basic_map_from_multi_aff(maff);
4272 map_i = isl_map_from_basic_map(bmap);
4273 map_i = isl_map_intersect_domain(map_i,
4274 isl_set_copy(pma->p[i].set));
4275 map = isl_map_union_disjoint(map, map_i);
4276 }
4277
4278 isl_pw_multi_aff_free(pma);
4279 return map;
4280}

4289 "isl_pw_multi_aff cannot be converted into an isl_set",do { isl_handle_error(isl_pw_multi_aff_get_ctx(pma), isl_error_invalid
